	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(center)"><date>Wednesday 16th</date><add>&#63;</add> <date>Shevat&#40;Feb&#41;&#44; 1865</date></p>
				<p>My friend and the friend of the Almighty&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I have received the manuscript but the <date>February</date> issue<lb/> only yesterday. In <date>January</date>&#44; you did not send me the usual ten copies.<lb/> Of the <date>February</date> number&#44; however&#44; you must be good enough to send me at<lb/> once 12&#45;15 copies&#44; so that I might send several to <placeName>Germany</placeName> on <date>Friday</date>.<lb/> Have you no opportunity to send it along with someone as you used to&#63;<lb/> For I should be glad to come and get them if you will send me the address<lb/> in <placeName>New York</placeName>. Otherwise&#44; send them to my home by express&#44; <placeName>112 West 25th <sic>ST.</sic>&#44;<lb/> near 7th Avenue</placeName>&#44; but please write the address clearly. Unfortunately my<lb/> speculation with my &#8220;<persName>Esther</persName>&#8221; did not succeed. You&#44; too&#44; did not want to<lb/> support me properly. I shall therefore send you&#44; tomorrow&#44; the trans&#45;<lb/>lation for publication in the &#8220;Occident&#8221;&#44; where it will therefore appear<add>&#63;</add><lb/> But should like to ask that you stereotype it&#44; but&#44; in any case&#44; to<lb/> make of it a separate audition. You therefore need not make the &#8220;Occident&#8221;<lb/> any larger.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have so much to speak to you about&#44; but you are so often<lb/> unapproachable. I heard that you were here last <date>Sunday</date> at a meeting of<lb/> the Delegates. I ran with my old feet to <persName>Sternberger</persName> and no one knew<lb/> about you.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Here there is again a great <add>&#63;</add>. In the <placeName>Henry Street</placeName><lb/> synagogue they want to imitate the <placeName>Green Street</placeName> Synagogue and put the<lb/> gentle dates on the gravestones. I am opposed and I have my reasons<lb/> and my views. I shall also come in conflict with <persName>Wise</persName> on account of<lb/> the burning of his heretical works. But I stand here like a lonely<lb/> shrub in the wilderness. What do people say about my warning&#63; The<lb/> passage against <persName>Wise</persName> and <persName>Einhorn</persName>&#44; you have translated exactly. I await<lb/> your answer by return post.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Sincerely yours&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Jonah of the house of Bondi</persName></p>
		</body>
